headline: Charles Schwab Boosts Dividend After Year of Strong Growth
summary: Charles Schwab  is giving its dividend a significant boost.  The board of the financial services company approved a 19% increase in its regular quarterly cash dividend to 32 cents a common share, the company announced late Thursday.  “This dividend increase reflects the Board’s confidence in our ability to continue to drive profitable growth through-the-cycle as we advance our ‘through clients’ eyes’ strategy,” Co-Chairman Walt Bettinger said in a statement.
